 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Miss-classification analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example we analyze the miss-classifications of the random shapelet forest and the nearest neighbour classifier."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "from wildboar.datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "from wildboar.ensemble import ShapeletForestClassifier, ShapeletForestEmbedding\n",
    "\n",
    "random_state = 1234"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we load a dataset and define the training and testing partitions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"Car\")\n",
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=random_state\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we define a pipeline that projects the dataset to a 2-dimensional plane using the shapelet forest embedding and pricipal component analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "f_embedding = make_pipeline(\n",
    "    ShapeletForestEmbedding(sparse_output=False, random_state=random_state),\n",
    "    PCA(n_components=2, random_state=random_state),\n",
    ")\n",
    "f_embedding.fit(x_train)\n",
    "x_embedding = f_embedding.transform(x_test)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we define the classifiers we want to train, test, analyze and plot."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.colorbar.Colorbar at 0x7fe0088bbaf0>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x432 with 9 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "classifiers = [\n",
    "    (\"Shapelet forest\", ShapeletForestClassifier(random_state=random_state)),\n",
    "    (\"Nearest neighbors\", KNeighborsClassifier()),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "classes = np.unique(y)\n",
    "n_classes = len(classes)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(\n",
    "    nrows=len(classifiers),\n",
    "    ncols=n_classes,\n",
    "    figsize=(3 * n_classes, 6),\n",
    "    sharex=True,\n",
    "    sharey=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "for i, (name, clf) in enumerate(classifiers):\n",
    "    clf.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "    y_pred = clf.predict(x_test)\n",
    "    probas = clf.predict_proba(x_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "    for k in range(n_classes):\n",
    "        if i == 0:\n",
    "            ax[i, k].set_title(\"Label: %r\" % classes[k])\n",
    "        if k == 0:\n",
    "            ax[i, k].set_ylabel(name)\n",
    "\n",
    "        ax[i, k].scatter(\n",
    "            x_embedding[:, 0],\n",
    "            x_embedding[:, 1],\n",
    "            c=\"black\",\n",
    "            alpha=0.2,\n",
    "            marker=\"x\",\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        mappable = ax[i, k].scatter(\n",
    "            x_embedding[y_pred == classes[k], 0],\n",
    "            x_embedding[y_pred == classes[k], 1],\n",
    "            c=probas[y_pred == classes[k], k],\n",
    "            marker=\"x\",\n",
    "            cmap=\"viridis\",\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        ax[i, k].scatter(\n",
    "            x_embedding[(y_test[y_test != y_pred] == classes[k]).nonzero()[0], 0],\n",
    "            x_embedding[(y_test[y_test != y_pred] == classes[k]).nonzero()[0], 1],\n",
    "            edgecolors=\"red\",\n",
    "            linewidths=2,\n",
    "            alpha=0.3,\n",
    "            facecolors=\"None\",\n",
    "            s=70,\n",
    "            marker=\"o\",\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "fig.colorbar(mappable, ax=ax, orientation=\"horizontal\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In the above figure, we see the time series as projected by PCA, colored according the predition probability of the corresponding label. Miss-labeled samples are circed in red."
   ]
  }
 ],
